        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 2 at 7:33PM CDT until May 2 at 8:15PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 732 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Mars Hills to Delta to near Goodwater, moving
east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Malone, Graham, Cleveland Crossroads, Dickert, Lake Wedowee, Morrison
Cross Roads, Newell, Barfield, R.L. Harris Dam, Roanoke, Woodland,
Tennant, Edwardsville, Trickem, Lake Cleburne, Heflin, Rock Mills,
Micaville, Big Springs, and Motley.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
